&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-is-regular-expression&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;markdownIt-Anchor&#34; href=&#34;#what-is-regular-expression&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt; What Is Regular Expression ?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regular Expression (RegExp) a sequence of symbols and characters expressing a string or pattern to be searched for within a longer piece of text. &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regular_expression&#34;&gt;Read More&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-can-a-regular-expression-be-used-for&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;markdownIt-Anchor&#34; href=&#34;#what-can-a-regular-expression-be-used-for&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt; What can a regular expression be used for ?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A regular expression can be a single character, or a more complicated pattern. Regular expressions can be used to perform all types of text search and text replace operations. /w3schools/i is a regular expression.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;which-is-the-best-example-of-a-regex&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;markdownIt-Anchor&#34; href=&#34;#which-is-the-best-example-of-a-regex&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Which is the best example of a regex ?&lt;/h2&gt;
